<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-06T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-06T09:00:00-05:00" n="1402" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1402">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/8–645: Telegram</note>
                        <head>No. 1402<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi>
                                (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-06T16:00:00+02:00">August 6, 1945—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4722. <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> tells me
                            confidentially that replies to the various notes I handed to him having
                            to do with the Potsdam Conference<note n="1" xml:id="d1402fn1"><ref target="#d1395">Documents Nos. 1395</ref>–<ref target="#d1400">1400</ref>.</note> will be handed to me within the next day or
                            two. He remarked that his government is very much upset over the
                            statements regarding reparations which they read in the Potsdam
                                communiqué.<note n="2" xml:id="d1402fn2">See <ref target="#d1384">document No. 1384</ref>, sections <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>
                                and <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>.</note> He said that they are also
                            much concerned about the article referring to the <pb facs="1749" n="1549" xml:id="pg_1549"/> possibility of setting up a central
                            government for Germany<note n="3" xml:id="d1402fn3">The reference is
                                probably to <ref target="#d1384">document No. 1384</ref>, section
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, paragraph (3)(i).</note> for they
                            take it to mean that it is the intention of the Soviet Government to
                            Sovietize all Germany as rapidly as they can do so.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_CJ1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>